This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Notice of bond forfeiture mailed to defendant. ($500.00 signature bond) LW

Defendant Keith L Cleveland not in court.  Attorney Imran Kurter in court for Keith L Cleveland.  Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for pretrial conference.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO COMMISSIONER. Court further orders that bail is forfeited.

Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 2 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders. 
Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY. 
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Keith L Cleveland appeared by video.  Attorney Douglas J. Rebholz appeared by video for Keith L Cleveland.  Attorney Amy Spanczak appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to RESERVE JUDGE, Branch 13.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned to Branch 13.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 25, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
